  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1303",
  "title": "Export strategy naming",
  "body": "We currently have something like:\n- `import {Range} from 'react-instantsearch';` => will render a slider\n- `import {Range} from 'react-instantsearch';` => Range.input will render an input, Range.connect is the generic connector\n\nAside from #1300, we have a naming problem because it should be obvious that Range is a slider by default.\n\nWe need to move to:\n\n``` js\nimport {\n  RangeSlider,\n  RangeInput,\n  rangeConnect\n} from 'react-instantsearch';\n```\n\nSingle namespace, clear separation, every export only import what he needs (connect does not loads the Slider CSS code for instance).\n\n**The following ↓↓↓ discussion and comments are no more relevant as for decision making. We aligned and this issue description is our final statement.**\n",
